# Pin TUF root metadata assets to byte-exact LF storage.
#
# The bundled Sigstore production root in `tuf/assets/sigstore_prod.root.json`
# carries a SHA-256 digest in `tuf/src/embedded.rs` that was computed over
# the upstream-provided bytes (LF line endings, as Sigstore publishes them).
# Without this rule git would round-trip the file through CRLF on
# Windows checkouts via `core.autocrlf=true`, breaking the digest test
# and the build-time integrity check.
#
# `binary` is the strongest guarantee: byte-for-byte preservation,
# never EOL-converted, never diff'd as text. We treat the asset as
# binary because that is what the trust claim requires.
tuf/assets/*.root.json binary
